<h2>Carlos's Tips</h2>

<table cellspacing="1" class="table">
<tr valign="bottom">
	<td><strong>Making Research Less Painful</strong></td>
	<td><strong>Planning, Timing & Keeping Things On Track</strong></td>
</tr>
<tr valign="top">
	<td width="50%">
<ul>
<li class="table_list">know what you're looking at</li>
<li class="table_list">email good citations and articles to yourself as you find them</li>
<li class="table_list">keep track of what you've done and what worked</li>
<li class="table_list">take good notes</li>
<li class="table_list">keep things in one place</li>
<li class="table_list">print out web pages that you plan to use as sources for your assignment</li>
</ul>
</td>
	<td width="50%">
<ul>
<li class="table_list">make sure you understand the assignment</li>
<li class="table_list">estimate how long your assignment will take and double it</li>
<li class="table_list">break your assignment down into small pieces & set deadlines for them</li>
<li class="table_list">get help with research if you need it</li>
<li class="table_list">leave yourself enough time to do the assignment</li>
<li class="table_list">bounce ideas around with people</li>
<li class="table_list">take advantage of the resources available to UCLA students</li>
</ul>

